</head>
<body class="bg-gradient-to-br from-pink-200 via-purple-100 to-pink-200 min-h-screen flex flex-col">

  <!-- Navbar -->
  <header class="flex justify-between items-center px-8 py-4 bg-white shadow-md">
    <h1 class="text-xl font-bold text-black">SheRises</h1>
    <nav class="flex space-x-8">
      <a href="/" class="text-pink-500 hover:text-pink-700 font-semibold">Home</a>
      <a href="/RightAndLaws" class="text-pink-500 hover:text-pink-700 font-semibold">Rights & Laws</a>
      <a href="/FirGuide" class="text-pink-500 hover:text-pink-700 font-semibold">Fir Guide</a>
      <a href="/FindHelp" class="text-pink-500 hover:text-pink-700 font-semibold">Find Help</a>
      <a href="/Blog" class="text-pink-500 hover:text-pink-700 font-semibold">Blog</a>
      <a href="/chatbot" class="text-pink-600 text-base hover:text-pink-800 font-semibold">Legal Assisstant</a>
    </nav>
  </header>

  <!-- Main Content -->
  <main class="flex-1 p-10">
    <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-purple-700 mb-6 text-center">How to File an FIR</h2>
    
    <!-- Intro -->
    <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 text-center max-w-3xl mx-auto mb-10">
      A First Information Report (FIR) is a written document prepared by the police when they receive information 
      about the commission of a cognizable offence. Here’s a step-by-step guide to help you.
    </p>

    <!-- Steps -->
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
      <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-xl shadow-md hover:shadow-xl transition">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-pink-600 mb-2">📌 Step 1: Visit Official Website</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700">Go to your State Police Official Website</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-xl shadow-md hover:shadow-xl transition">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-pink-600 mb-2">📝 Step 2: Choose category</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700">Look for "Citizen Services" / "Lodge e-FIR" / "Report Lost Article".</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-xl shadow-md hover:shadow-xl transition">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-pink-600 mb-2">✍️ Step 3: Fill Details</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700">Fill in details online – incident type, time, place, personal info, etc.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-xl shadow-md hover:shadow-xl transition">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-pink-600 mb-2">📄 Step 4: Submit FIR</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700">Submit & receive acknowledgement – you’ll get an FIR number and a copy via email/SMS.Track FIR status online</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Important Notes -->
    <div class="mt-12 p-6 bg-purple-100 border border-purple-300 rounded-xl">
      <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-purple-700 mb-3">⚖️ Important Rights</h3>
      <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-700 space-y-2">
        <li>Police cannot refuse to register an FIR in case of a cognizable offence.</li>
        <li>Women can lodge an FIR at any police station (Zero FIR concept).</li>
        <li>You can request a female police officer to record your statement.</li>
        <li>FIR can also be filed online in some states.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <!-- Extra Resource -->
    <div class="mt-10 text-center">
      <a href="https://delhipolice.gov.in/" 
         target="_blank" 
         class="bg-pink-500 hover:bg-pink-600 text-white px-6 py-3 rounded-lg shadow-lg transition">
        🚓 File FIR Online (Official Police Websites)
      </a>
    </div>
  </main>

